# 🦠 COVID-19 Global Data Analysis

This project analyzes global COVID-19 data to understand the pandemic’s progression, impact across countries, mortality trends, and recovery patterns using Python and visual analytics.

---

## 📌 Objectives

- Track daily and total confirmed, recovered, and death cases  
- Compare country-wise COVID-19 statistics  
- Visualize global and regional trends in the pandemic  
- Generate insights to support public health and policy decisions

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies

- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Matplotlib, Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

---

## 📊 Key Insights

- India, USA, and Brazil were among the most affected countries  
- Recovery rates improved significantly after initial waves  
- Death rates varied sharply across continents and timeframes  
- Visualizations reveal patterns in daily case spikes and flattening curves

---

## 📂 How to Run

1. Clone this repository or download the files  
2. Open `Covid_19_project.ipynb` in Jupyter Notebook or Google Colab  
3. Run all cells to explore the complete analysis and graphs

---

